caption: I was pleasantly surprised by the food here. I work near here but never thought to try this small restaurant located next to a massage parlor and a moped rental shop. For appetizers, we ordered the spring rolls. It came with 3 pieces cut up in half.  The price was a little high at a little over $7, but they tasted great and is probably one of the better spring rolls I've ever eaten. For my main, I ordered the oxtail soup. Wow! The bowl was huge and was filled with 4 huge oxtails. The meat was really tender and flavorful. The broth was tasty and I like how the soup came with a lot of veggies. We came early so getting a table was fast but as soon as we were seated the place started to fill up. Great little restaurant with a friendly staff and good food!

BEST one so far, even though I am not a pho lover, I think it is the pho spot in Oahu. a authentic Vietnamese friend told me this spot. Yes!!! He is right.   High recommended one.  The staff are super nice.
Probably my favorite Pho restaurant on the island.  The broth is tasty and they give a lot of vegetables to go along with it.  The staff are all super friendly.

If you are looking to support a sweet, local family then this is your place!! The staff are so friendly and the pho was just what we needed on yesterday’s rainy day. very delicious. the owner (liem) took time out of her night to come out and talk with us. she was so very friendly and we all left smiling. she even tried to chase us down after we forgot a bag in her restaurant. she went above and beyond! thank you, liem!

The Pho was so good that I forgot the basil, and the bean sprouts! This place is  good, and reasonably priced for Hawaii! The owner even came out to wish all of us a Happy New Year!

The flavor was really good but I ordered rare steak and because my broth wasnt very hot, my rare steak didnt quite cook nicely. However, I probably could have asked them to heat it up for me, or gotten extra hot soup on the side for my rare steak, but I was too hungry and couldn't be bothered hahaha. Because of limited capacity, we did have to wait a tiny bit, but I super appreciated the woman (owner? Idk) who kept coming outside to check on us and make sure we knew she hadn't forgotten about us.

You will not be disappointed! You know it's LEGIT when they ask you if you want your meat on the side uncooked, when they have culantro, and when they have the good chili oil. And most importantly, the broth is really good!

This is one of the very best places for pho and lots of other dishes! You get lime, NOT lemon with your pho, the broth is well-balanced in flavor and not too salty, whatever beef you order is always tasty. Don't stop there, try their crispy and flavorful spring rolls, rice vermicelli bowls, oxtail soup and pad thai, just to name a few. I appreciate how perfectly seasoned their pad thai always is, with just the right balance of ingredients. The sauce doesn't taste ketchup based. I like to order the chicken and tofu pad thai. Usually when you order this at other places, the chicken is dry, overcooked, flavorless and the tofu is pretty much the same. Here they manage to cook both chicken and tofu that is tender, juicy, and well-infused with flavor. Service is excellent, prices are reasonable. Try this place!
Authentic, amazing pho. Take-out is a great option as they package everything (including the raw beef) separate from the broth to avoid overcooking. The broth is perfect. Great portion sizes too.

I found this place during the COVID pandemic, and thank goodness I did. Incredibly affordable pho, especially for the serving portion and quality. Plus, takeout orders are well thought out and all provisions are provided separately to keep any toppings from getting soft.

On the recommendation of a Vietnamese friend, I had dinner here. The Pho was good and the service was courteous. Closing time is at 9 pm on the night I visited so they were in a bit of rush to have me finish and leave. As with most Pho restaurants, this place is not licensed to serve alcoholic beverages.

Excellent first experience with pho.  As such I have nothing to compare it to but this was some great food.  The restaurant has a small and friendly atmosphere that is doubled by the friendliness of the staff.  I explained that it was my first time having pho.  The waitress was GREAT and explained things to me such as the various herbs brought with my bowl.  She even mixed up a condiment combination that she said was popular so that I could try it.  That is exceptional service!  Pho Bistro is also an obvious local favorite as I was clearly the only tourist eating there at the time.  Get a regular size if you have never had pho before. The pho broth was still boiling so I threw the meat in and it cooked before out eyes. Our friends from New Zealand remarked that we were having a pho picnic at the pool. The pho was amazing. I loved how we were able to throw everything in. I just wished they would have warned us about it.
